*  = represent zero or more characters
? = represent a single character
[] = represent a range of character

calvin@localhost:~$ rm abs*
this means remove everything start with abs

calvin@localhost:~$ touch abs{1..9}
this means create abs1, abs2, abc3 ..... abc9. it creates nine files

calvin@localhost:~$ ls -l abs*
this means i want to list everthing start with abc

calvin@localhost:~$ ls -l *xyz
list all the files that ends with xyz

calvin@localhost:~$ ls -l ?bcd*
list all the files no matter what is the first letter but after first latter bcd

calvin@localhost:~$ rm *xy*
it says remove every file that has x and y in it, x and y has to be together.
